# bp0.work — Application repository rules

This git repository contains **implementation code only**. Do **not** commit documentation that describes architecture, APIs, deployment, operations, or how the system works.

## Non-negotiables

| Rule | Detail |
|------|--------|
| **Scope** | Edit only implementation paths (`accfin/`, `finance-ui/`, `platform-admin-ui/`, `client-admin-ui/`) |
| **No docs in git** | Do not add or restore `platform_dox/`, `*.md` READMEs, runbooks, incident playbooks, `accfin/docs/` specification copies, or design-suite excerpts |
| **No spec in git** | Numbered design documents (`00`–`21`), OpenAPI mirrors, and version-history tables stay on the developer machine only |
| **Version bump** | Every PR must bump `accfin/app/core/config.py` → `Settings.version` and the **Release version** line in the repo root `README.md` to the same deploy tag (e.g. `0.14.22-redis-socket-keepalive`). Update local `platform_dox/` version history in the same change set (not committed to git). |

When design authority is required, use the **local specification workspace** outside this git root. That content is not pushed to GitHub.
